OL,6,FThe Bishop of Carlisle Rev Rob Saner-
OL,7,FHaigh unveiled a memorial garden at
OL,8,FParkside Cemetery and described St
OL,9,FMonica's mother and baby home as a
OL,10,Fplace of "pain, rejection and
OL,11,Fheartache".
OL,13,FSpeaking at the ceremony held on
OL,14,FFriday, he said: "This is a place for
OL,15,Fthose who have lost their children and
OL,16,Floved ones. (St Monica's) should have
OL,17,Fbeen sanctuary ... but for many it
OL,18,Fbecame a place of pain, rejection and
OL,19,Fheartache. They were not trated well
OL,20,Fby the church and I am truly sorry for
OL,21,Fthat."
