OL,6,FIn post-war Britain an estimated
OL,7,F250,000 women were sent away to
OL,8,Finstitutions run by religious
OL,9,Forganisations and the state where they
OL,10,Fwere pressured and coerced to put
OL,11,Ftheir babies up for adoption.
OL,13,FOther infants died due to mistreatment
OL,14,For poor care.
OL,16,FMr Hindley told ITV News: "Judith was
OL,17,F17 at the time and she told me she was
OL,18,Fforced to clean floors and kitchens
OL,19,Fwhile heavily pregnant. They were
OL,20,Fbeing punished."
